        "whyGood": "Only 37,018 miles on a 2008 — this top, headliner, and rear window have barely been stressed. At 9 miles from Media it is practically a local car. CarGurus Great Deal badge confirms it is priced below market. The base Kappa is still genuinely fun to drive and 37k miles means the top rubber and seals are near-new.",
        "whatToVerify": "Operate the soft top through 3+ full open/close cycles and listen for motor hesitation; check the header latches positively. Inspect the rear plastic window for crazing or seam separation. Check rocker panels and sills for rust (Solstice rockers are notorious). Verify tire age (DOT code) — 30k miles over 17 years may mean extended storage periods. Check brake fluid and coolant condition.",
        "bottomLine": "Lowest-mileage fun car in the batch — see this one first."
      },
