        "imageUrl": "https://platform.cstatic-images.com/large/in/v2/e72144f1-aead-598b-81fe-dde1a688b59e/50373c5d-5c8c-4f92-a2a7-1ede447edece/yBxA2qv8nNGTafj1jDEMsCRPQHA.jpg",
        "whyGood": "GXP means the turbocharged 260hp 2.0L Ecotec — a completely different car from the base Solstice. At $8,195 with 88k miles and a Great Deal badge on CarGurus (same car listed at $8,590), this is the best price-to-fun ratio in the entire batch. No accidents, clean title confirmed via Cars.com filter.",
        "whatToVerify": "Top through full cycles plus rocker rust check (same as all Solstice variants). Additionally: verify boost holds under hard acceleration (LNF wastegate can rattle), check for oil consumption between changes, inspect intercooler couplings for cracks. Timing chain is oil-pressure sensitive — confirm regular oil change history.",
        "bottomLine": "Best bang-for-buck turbo roadster in the batch — GXP at this price is genuinely a deal."
